# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore any .python-version file.
#   For a project, you usually wish to include it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install them on other platforms. In this case, you should probably ignore Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/project/#commit-the-pdm-lock-file
